cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the task of synonym discovery in clinical data, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning and statistical methods, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of aggregated co-occurrence counts suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DB (Databases) and the focus on synonym discovery suggests that it may be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
